# Git commit author email

Vercel blocks deploys when commit email is not linked to GitHub.

**Always use this author/committer email for commits in this repo:**
- Email: `asra.saeed@outlook.com`
- Name: `Asra Saeed`

When committing via shell, set env vars explicitly:

```bash
GIT_AUTHOR_NAME="Asra Saeed" \
GIT_AUTHOR_EMAIL="asra.saeed@outlook.com" \
GIT_COMMITTER_NAME="Asra Saeed" \
GIT_COMMITTER_EMAIL="asra.saeed@outlook.com" \
git commit ...
```

Never commit with auto-generated hostname emails (e.g. `*@*.ht.home`).

Do not change global git config; the repo has local `user.email` / `user.name` set.
